<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09015b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09015b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09015b"> 15(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> science / magnify injustice till it / is intolerable</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">I think then that the tendency of applied <mark>science</mark> is to <mark>magnify injustices until they become too intolerable</mark> to be borne, and the average man whom all the prophets and poets could not move, turns at least and extinguishes the evil at its source. Marx&apos; theory of industrial evolution is a particular example of this tendency, though it does not in the least follow that his somewhat artificial solution of the problem will be adopted. <small> J. B. S. Haldane, <a name="DAED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DAED"><cite title="source">Dedalus</cite></a> (1923) 85f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
